title: Position Rifle Shooting
description:
Position Rifle Shooting is the classic book on competition rifle shooting. It does an excellent job of explaining the four basic shooting positions, this is not a "do it this way" book, it shows several variations to the positions and encourages the reader to experiment, it also emphasises the importance of experimenting and making changes to ones shooting in a methodical manner so one can determine what actually works. 

This torrent is a scan of the book in Jpeg format.

1973, Pullum and Hanenkrat
